Text.Value: Thank you for giving me a second chance.
Bhaal tried to extinguish thee, but his wrath is imprecise. He only succeeded in killing the part of thee he knew.
Thou hast defied Bhaal, thy liege and father, and in doing so hast earned a place among champions and heroes.
But, alas, thy courage was in opposition to the divine cosmology that bound thee to the Lord of Murder.

EditorData.stateContext: Player's standing in Bhaal Temple, Withers looking down at the body

Text.Value: Did you know my nature all this time?
It took time, but at the last, thine independence of heart overshadowed thy murderous mind.

EditorData.logicalname: PLAYER ONLY RESISTED BHAAL AT THE END

Text.Value: Without you, I'd likely be long dead. Count me extremely grateful you're still here.
Congratulations. That was hard-fought and well-deserved. You're free.

EditorData.NodeContext: Sincere. Proud of a companion who faced down their demons

Text.Value: The heart of a saviour hath overshadowed the mind of a murderer.

EditorData.InternalNodeContext: Withers would have awoken the victim if Orin hadn't killed them at this point.

Text.Value: I share thine enthusiasm. In mine own manner.
My old memories and my past self - I can never get them back?
I can only give what thou hast earned.
Greet the bloodless dawn, child of none.

EditorData.AnimationTags: *REUSE*[PLAYER] Awaken anims from CAMP_DarkUrge_Bloodwedding_SD<CodyM: for player standing up>
EditorData.CinematicNodeContext: DU stands again, looks towards the vacant symbol of Bhaal in the temple

Text.Value: That part, Bhaal could not extinguish. And so instead of destroying thee, he hath made thee anew.
*You can conduct atrocities whenever you please and get a peaceful night's sleep.*
A hero has risen from a legacy of death.

EditorData.InternalNodeContext: If Orin didn't kill them, Withers would have awoken them by this point.

Text.Value: It must be said - because of you, I still breathe. Because of you, I still battle. I am not one to show gratitude, but - *ahem* - thank you.
I just want to rest - death seemed so peaceful.
All their names are written. One day, if thou truly wishest, I will show thee, and we shall remember them together.
Well done - I knew your true nature remained, beneath those dark impulses. You are your true self, at last.

EditorData.stateContext: Player is seated in Bhaal Temple, Withers looking down at the body

Text.Value: *After all, you have not been turned good.*
If thou couldst recall in full every barbarity thou hadst committed, every tragedy thou hadst authored... wouldst thou truly want to?
A scribe, a seneschal - a keeper of records. And now, thine advocate, both here, and in the City of the Dead.
Do not thank me - trust in thy courage, and the conviction of thy companions.
*If you plan to command the world, no one will suspect a thing until it is too late.*
Thou hast vanquished thine Urge.
You're the author of your own tale now - well done.
Relish: with Bhaal gone, your sins will at last be truly yours.
This intervention, the reclamation of thy soul, is beyond mine ordinary remit. But thou art extraordinary, and so are these times.
*Now, you may yet rule, and rule unhindered, rid of your domineering Father.*
*There is so little of you left.*
Minsc had his doubts about you, little Slayer, but Boo had none!
I know all, but to state truths is to interfere, for the minds of mortals are easily swayed. My place, for the most part, is to observe.
Was there ever any doubt? You are a champion. You overcome.
Thy fight is not over, and it is thy fight, for one who can look upon Bhaal and oppose him can survive any crisis.

EditorData.CinematicNodeContext: Withers starts to magically heal the DU

Text.Value: It is a dishonour to my victims to not recall their names.
Today, thou art born anew.
Better not to know. Better to forget.
Thou art now faithless - godless - and doomed to wander the Fugue Plane for eternity.
You get to start over. To be the person you want to be - not what someone else made you to be.
*There is nothing left to do, but write yourself anew.*
*But your journey is not over.*

EditorData.AnimationTags: [PLAYER] lying dead on the ground, inhales sharply. <CodyM>
EditorData.CinematicNodeContext: Dark Urge opens their eyes, sharp intake of breath

Text.Value: I think it would drive me mad.
Thy path is clear. You must save Baldur's Gate.
A triumph most deserved. Well done.

EditorData.stateContext: Player's corpse lying in Bhaal Temple, Withers looking down at the body

Text.Value: I, too, still hold some power, and I invest a portion of it in thee, who hath challenged the gods and now liveth to tell of it.
Indeed. And thou art recently cured of one form of madness - let us not exchange it for another.
Nothing is ever truly forgotten - I will remember them always - but thou mayst turn thy mind to the future.
Our enemies don't stand a chance.
Who are you?
You fought, and you prevailed. Your future will be what you make of it.
Worry - so much of your brain is beyond repair.
*For the first time in over a century, silence falls over the Bhaal Temple. No chants, no screams, no prayers.*

EditorData.CinematicNodeContext: The DU is dead, corpse in the centre of the temple

Text.Value: Cured at last! Cured!
Happy birthday, soldier.
*In the end, your own death brought you more joy than any you wrought on this land. You are slipping into peaceful oblivion.*
I have no idea what to do.
So rise, Challenger of Gods, and prepare for battle once more. Death will not claim thee whilst I endure.

EditorData.AnimationTags: *REUSE*[PLAYER] Awaken anims from CAMP_DarkUrge_Bloodwedding_SD<CodyM: from player sitting in their bedroll>

Text.Value: There is no true rest for those like thee, faithless. But when victory is won, I swear I shall find thee a home.
I will not permit that, though all the powers of life and death dictate that it should be so.
A genuine pleasure to meet you again, my friend.

EditorData.NodeContext: Understated warmth - she's not overly sentimental, but is genuinely proud of us - we resisted our evil bloodline.

Text.Value: You did it. You're free. I'm so godsdamn proud of you!
The sole way to atone for thine actions is to do better, in a new dawn. That dawn has come.
I deserve to die - for all the evil I have done.
As it was, so it is again.
He's right, you're no monster. You've saved me more times than I can count.

EditorData.stateContext: Player's corpse lying in Bhaal Temple

Text.Value: Thank you.
I'd be worm food if it wasn't for you. Thank you.
But there is a new part of you that hath grown during thy travels.
*For now they believe you sweet and innocent, having triumphed against such evil.*
The Urge that drove thee to terrible acts. The spark of brutality that made thee his.

Synopsis:
Orin, Chosen of Bhaal lays dead by the Dark Urge. Bhaal has given his terms to the Dark Urge. Players has rejected Bhaal and died in the process.

Players will reappear in camp.
